{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50a0dda2-aed1-4204-b2d9-d4abfe46a567","content":"I can help point you in the right direction! The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them — so it won't apply here.\n\nFor **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, use one of these tools:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — .NET CLI tool\n   - `dumpheap`, `printexception`, `clrstack`, `threads` commands\n\n2. **`lldb`** (Linux/macOS) with the SOS plugin\n   - `dotnet-sos install` then `lldb -c <file.dmp>`\n\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** (Windows)\n\n**Quick triage commands** inside `dotnet-dump analyze`:\n```\n> printexception        # show last exception\n> clrstack -all         # managed call stacks\n> threads               # list all threads\n> dumpheap -stat        # heap summary\n```\n\nInstall the tool if needed:\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n```\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if you can provide the path?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25c26b5e-d2e9-4514-9b99-055938b5c983","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. Let me provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"4185:195805:62C5987:6C0E7D8:69F164C0"},"id":"2b15f0b2-c6ec-4851-82b3-259b18bd3ca6","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:54:28.030Z","parentId":"e7baac52-6cdb-4d16-b04b-51c32e332c21"}
